 Kourtney Kardashian and Travis Baker | USA Today Newly wedded Kourtney Kardashian has added her husband’s last name “Barker” to her Instagram account. The reality TV star officially added her new last name to her Instagram on Monday after she married beau Travis Barker in a lavish wedding ceremony over the weekend in Italy. Her bio now reads “Kourtney Kardashian Barker.” While it is not clear if she has changed her name legally or plans to, Kourtney has, however, retained her original Instagram handle @kourtneykadash. Kourtney and Travis said “I do” at their D&G themed wedding celebration at Castello Brown on Sunday with their family and friends in attendance. A week ago, the couple had legally gotten married in Santa Barbara, Calif. Kourtney Kardashian Photo Instagram Kourtney wore a short white dress at her Italian wedding with a veil emblazoned with the image of the Virgin Mary, inspired by one of Travis’ tattoos. Her ex Scott Disick was not in attendance, but two of her kids, Mason and Penelope, attended the grand ceremony. Other Kardashians were dressed in Dolce & Gabanna ensembles. Kim and Khloe rocked black maxi dresses, while Kylie and Kendall wore flower printed maxi dresses. Kourtney Kardashian Photo Instagram For the wedding reception, Kourtney changed into a black ensemble. Kardashian’s grandmother, Maa mony Jo “MJ” Campbell, and Barker’s father, Randy, also attended the ceremony. This is Kourtney’s first marriage and Travis’ third, as he was previously married to Moakler from 2004 to 2008 and Melissa Kennedy from 2001 to 2002.